fix: Make firstName and lastName optional for user signup
This commit updates the UserCreate Pydantic model in the backend to make firstName and lastName optional fields. This increases the flexibility of the /api/auth/signup endpoint and aims to reduce 400 Bad Request errors that may occur if these fields are not provided by the frontend during signup.
The username generation logic has been confirmed to handle these optional name fields.

fix: Enhance auth stability with static SECRET_KEY and confirm error reporting
This commit addresses potential authentication failures by ensuring the JWT SECRET_KEY is static, preventing token invalidation across server restarts. It also confirms that frontend error reporting for login is already adequate.
Key changes: - Modified backend/app/core/config.py to use a fixed default for SECRET_KEY, with strong recommendations to override via environment variables for production. This is critical for token stability. - Reviewed frontend login error handling in src/pages/Login.tsx, confirming that it already displays specific error messages from the backend, which aids in diagnostics. - Previous refactoring of the /me endpoint's data retrieval path (using a new get_current_user_data dependency) was also incorporated.

fix: Resolve login failure and address ESLint warnings
This commit addresses a critical login failure and cleans up ESLint warnings and TypeScript errors in the frontend application.
Fixes: - Resolved login failure by: - Adding a new GET /api/auth/me endpoint to the backend to fetch authenticated user details. - Modifying the frontend getCurrentUser function in api.ts to use this endpoint and removing a problematic localStorage fallback. - Ensuring AuthContext correctly handles errors from getCurrentUser, clearing session data if user fetching fails. - Made the fetchApi function in src/lib/api.ts generic (fetchApi<T>) to improve type safety for API responses. - Updated all call sites of fetchApi throughout the frontend (Settings.tsx, Activity.tsx, Profile.tsx, and within api.ts) to use the new generic signature with appropriate expected types. This resolved a TypeScript error in Settings.tsx. - Removed unused Lucide icon imports from src/pages/Settings.tsx, addressing ESLint warnings.
